noun.description: The action of gushing out; an effusive or passionate outburst.

origin: Early 19th century; earliest use found in Mary Russell Mitford (1787–1855), playwright and writer. From out- + gushing, after to gush out or outgush<br>mid 16th century; earliest use found in Edmund Spenser (?1552–1599), poet and administrator in Ireland. From out- + gush + -ing, after to gush out or outgush.
